title: Grateful Dead Live at Portland International Speedway on 1979-06-30
lineage: MAC >> Nakamichi CR7a => Korg MR-1000 >> DSF [1-bit 5.6448 MHz Stereo] >> Korg MR-1000 => Korg AudioGate >> WAV [24/96]
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, Candyman, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Tennessee Jed, Looks Like Rain, Deal

Set 2

I Need A Miracle-> Bertha-> Good Lovin', Friend Of The Devil, Estimated Prophet-> He's Gone-> Drums-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: One More Saturday Night

Other artist(s): McGuinn, Clark & Hillman, David Bromberg

reviews.review_text:
Best source! Out of all the different AUDs available for this show, including one transferred by Charlie Miller, this source is the best. The instrument separation, bass, and overall sound quality sounds superior. 

As for the show, I love the first few months of Brent, but the band was just settling into its new sound. Turn to November/December shows for the best from this year; however, don't overlook these earlier gems.
